# churn-prediction-system

A full-stack customer churn prediction system powered by an XGBoost classifier trained on the IBM Telco Customer Churn dataset. Enter a customer profile and get an instant churn probability, risk level, and multi-chart analytics dashboard.

---
 
## Features
 
- **XGBoost classifier** trained with randomized hyperparameter search (60 iterations, 5-fold stratified CV)
- **Youden's J threshold tuning** — optimal decision threshold computed from the ROC curve rather than defaulting to 0.5
- **Early stopping** on a held-out validation split to prevent overfitting
- **Engineered features**: `AvgMonthlySpend`, `LongTermCustomer`
- **Real-time analytics dashboard** — radar chart, probability gauge, factor breakdown, customer vs. dataset benchmark
- **Input validation** with per-field error messages on the frontend
---
 
## Project Structure
 
```
churn-intelligence/
├── src/
│   ├── main.jsx              # React entry point
│   ├── App.jsx               # Root component
│   ├── ChurnPredictor.jsx    # Main UI — form, result panel, analytics dashboard
│   └── index.css             # Global styles
├── app.py                    # Flask REST API (/predict, /health)
├── train.py                  # Model training script
├── model.pkl                 # Trained XGBoost pipeline (generated by train.py)
├── threshold.pkl             # Optimal decision threshold (generated by train.py)
├── WA_Fn-UseC_-Telco-Customer-Churn.csv  # Training dataset
├── index.html
├── package.json
├── vite.config.js
└── requirements.txt
```
 
