## Getting Started
 
### Prerequisites
 
- Python 3.10+
- Node.js 18+
---
 
### 1. Clone the repository
 
```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/churn-intelligence.git
cd churn-intelligence
```
 
### 2. Train the model (or use the included `.pkl` files)
 
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
python train.py
```
 
Outputs `model.pkl` and `threshold.pkl` in the project root. Training takes ~2–5 minutes.
 
### 3. Start the Flask backend
 
```bash
python app.py
```
 
API available at `http://localhost:5000`.
 
### 4. Start the React frontend
 
```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```
 
Open `http://localhost:5173` in your browser.
 
---
 
## API Reference
 
### `POST /predict`
 
**Request body:**
 
```json
{
  "tenure": 12,
  "Contract": "Month-to-month",
  "MonthlyCharges": 75.50,
  "TotalCharges": 906.00,
  "TechSupport": "No",
  "OnlineSecurity": "No",
  "InternetService": "Fiber optic",
  "PaymentMethod": "Electronic check",
  "Dependents": "No"
}
```
 
**Response:**
 
```json
{
  "churn_probability": 0.8241,
  "churn_prediction": "Churn",
  "risk_level": "High Risk",
  "threshold_used": 0.3817
}
```
 
Risk levels: `Low Risk` (< 0.4) · `Medium Risk` (0.4–0.7) · `High Risk` (≥ 0.7)
 
### `GET /health`
 
```json
{ "status": "ok", "threshold": 0.3817 }
```
 
---
 
## Model Details
 
| Attribute | Value |
|---|---|
| Algorithm | XGBoost (`binary:logistic`) |
| CV strategy | Stratified K-Fold (k=5) |
| Hyperparameter search | RandomizedSearchCV, 60 iterations |
| Threshold selection | Youden's J statistic (max TPR−FPR) |
| Class imbalance handling | `scale_pos_weight` ≈ 2.77 |
| Early stopping | 30 rounds on validation AUC |
 
**Features used:**
 
| Feature | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `tenure` | Numeric | Months as a customer |
| `MonthlyCharges` | Numeric | Charges per month |
| `TotalCharges` | Numeric | Total amount charged to the customer over their entire subscription period|
| `AvgMonthlySpend` | Engineered | `TotalCharges / (tenure + 1)` |
| `LongTermCustomer` | Engineered | Binary flag: `tenure > 24` |
| `Contract` | Categorical | One-hot encoded |
| `InternetService` | Categorical | One-hot encoded |
| `OnlineSecurity` | Categorical | One-hot encoded |
| `TechSupport` | Categorical | One-hot encoded |
| `PaymentMethod` | Categorical | One-hot encoded |
| `Dependents` | Binary | Label encoded |
 
---
 
## Dataset
 
[IBM Telco Customer Churn](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/blastchar/telco-customer-churn) — 7,043 customers, ~26.5% churn rate.

